AMERICAN NEGOTIATORS will be in Beijing this week to finalise a trade deal. What’s left to be agreed, and what are the sticking points? Also, America’s shale boom has given it leverage in international oil markets. How will it use its power? And we look at a foul-smelling Egyptian delicacy that has the potential to kill. Runtime: 21 min.    Listen on: Apple Podcasts | Spotify | Google | Stitcher | TuneIn